---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";

const headings = [
    { depth: 2, slug: "prerequisites", text: "Prerequisites" },
    { depth: 2, slug: "1-installation", text: "1. Installation" },
    { depth: 2, slug: "2-create-a-project", text: "2. Create a Project" },
    { depth: 2, slug: "3-start-development", text: "3. Start Development" },
    {
        depth: 2,
        slug: "4-your-first-component",
        text: "4. Your First Component",
    },
];
---

<DocsLayout title="Quick Start" headings={headings}>
    <h1>Quick Start Guide</h1>

    <p>Get up and running with Snakeskin in less than 5 minutes.</p>

    <h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-300">
        <li>Python 3.8+</li>
        <li>Node.js 16+ (for tooling)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="1-installation">1. Installation</h2>

    <p>Install the package via pip:</p>

    <CodeBlock code="pip install snakeskin-xplnhub" language="bash" />

    <h2 id="2-create-a-project">2. Create a Project</h2>

    <p>Scaffold a new project using the CLI:</p>

    <CodeBlock code="snakeskin create my-app\ncd my-app" language="bash" />

    <h2 id="3-start-development">3. Start Development</h2>

    <p>Run the development server:</p>

    <CodeBlock code="snakeskin dev" language="bash" />

    <p>Visit <code>http://localhost:3000</code> to see your app!</p>

    <h2 id="4-your-first-component">4. Your First Component</h2>

    <p>Edit <code>src/components/App.py</code>:</p>

    <CodeBlock
        code={`from snakeskin.framework import Component

class App(Component):
    def render(self):
        return """
        <div class="p-10 font-sans">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neon-green">Hello Snakeskin!</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-white">Edit this file to see changes instantly.</p>
        </div>
        """`}
        language="python"
        title="src/components/App.py"
    />
</DocsLayout>
